description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NHSP Hospital Cleaner&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title and Grade:&lt;/strong&gt;Domestic Staff Band 2&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location/Trust:&lt;/strong&gt;Nottingham University Hospitals NHS Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department Covered:&lt;/strong&gt;Cleaning Services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locations:&lt;/strong&gt;Queens Medical Centre (NG7 2UH)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay Rates &lt;/strong&gt;£9.21 per hour + accrued holiday pay&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shift Pattern: &lt;/strong&gt;5 days per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mon-Fri. Shift times - 06.00 – 14.00 or 14:00 - 22:00&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duration:&lt;/strong&gt; Ongoing Temporary (subject to reviews)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role: Domestic, Cleaning Staff&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are you approachable and a team player?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do you have previous experience as a cleaner?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can you commit to shifts Mon- Fri 06.00 – 14.00 or 14:00 - 22:00 ?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are you a person passionate about health care and want to make a difference?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If so, would you like to be part of a Trust that value, recognise and celebrate staff members and are a person passionate about health care and want to make a difference?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nottingham University Hospitals NHS Trust,are now one of the biggest and busiest NHS Trusts in the country and provide services to over 2.5 million residents of Nottingham, its surrounding communities, and a further 3-4 million people from across the region that need to use the specialist services we provide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have long term placement opportunities available for Domestic Staff at Nottingham University NHS Trust specifically who will be required to undertake the following.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be part of a Cleaning Services team that provides and always maintains the highest standard of service to patients, visitors and staff, ensuring at all times the highest degree of cleanliness, safety and care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Undertakes allocated tasks in a flexible, efficient manner working within defined rotas and work schedules according to Trust and departmental policies and procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;General responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;include the following. List not exhaustive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cleaning of all hard and soft floors, furniture, fixtures, fittings and surfaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cleaning of all sanitary, bathroom and shower facilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Replenishment of disposable commodities, i.e. toilet rolls, soap, gel and hand towels as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Removal of waste from wards and departments to designated collection points.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Making up of on-call and relatives overnight stay beds.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ad hoc cleaning of spillages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Changing of bed curtains, window curtains and screen curtains&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cleaning of infected room/bays in accordance with NUH Infection Control &amp; Prevention Policy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Receive, check and put away cleaning materials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Informing the Ward Team/Cleaning Services Team Leaders if any equipment is in need of maintenance and repair&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will give you an edge in applying for this position?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;COSHH awareness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;worked as cleaners or domestic assistants in NHS / medical environment previously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS conflict resolution training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of working in a healthcare-type environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In return for your hard work commitment NHS Professionals (NHSP) can offer you some fantastic benefits: –&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive Pay Rates - work this week, get paid next week!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;First choice of placements at over 50 NHS Trusts in England&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dedicated consultants&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working options&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free DBS and free training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build holiday allowance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support when you need it – 24/7 365 days&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stakeholder pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who are NHS Professionals?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working through the NHSP bank means Trusts don’t have to rely on expensive agencies. Right now, we have over 126,000 members registered on our bank from various roles, grades and specialities, saving the NHS over £70 million each year. This money is then reinvested back into the NHS. We look forward to hearing from you soon&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Disclaimer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Professionals (NHSP), owned by the Department of Health and Social Care (DHSC), works in partnership with hospital trusts to provide a bank of highly skilled temporary workers who want to work flexibly within the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note, you will be contacted by email throughout the recruitment process, so please check your emails, including your junk/spam regularly. We regret we cannot contact everyone who is not selected for an interview, therefore if you do not hear from us within 21 days after submitting your application, please assume you have not been successful on this occasion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
